{{Quote|Talk to random people for 2 minutes. Please use an optimized avatar!}}
'''No Time Two Talk''' is a cross-platform [[Special:MyLanguage/worlds|world]] based on Omegle<ref>https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Omegle</ref> that pairs random users in one-on-one 2 minute conversations based on shared interests encouraging getting to know other users quickly and making friends.

==Rounds==

===Normal rounds===
The round starts with each user being randomly paired up for a 2-minute conversation with another user. They can see each other's interests and start talking. If both users agree, they can extend the conversation for an additional two minutes. Users can leave the conversation at any time by walking through the door.

===Group rounds===
Every 20 minutes, all players will be teleported to a large group area where they can meet and chat with anyone or continue conversations that ran out of time. You can opt-out of group rounds in the options menu.

